name: Houston Weather
summary: As Hurricane Beryl made landfall in Texas, Houston experienced severe impacts. The storm caused widespread power outages, with over 2.7 million homes and businesses without electricity. Tragically, the death toll from the hurricane has risen. Beryl brought heavy rains and tropical storm force winds, leading to flooding and damage throughout the Houston area. The path of the storm included Katy and Cypress, where residents braced for significant impacts. The storm's effects were felt even in downtown Houston, as captured in videos. Despite the challenges, the Houston region remained resilient, with authorities and residents preparing for the heavy rains and potential flooding brought by Beryl.

name: Power outage Houston
summary: Hurricane Beryl has wreaked havoc on Houston's power grid, plunging over 2.2 million residents into darkness. CenterPoint Energy, the city's primary electricity provider, has been plagued by outages, with over 1 million customers still without power. The company's outage map has been unreliable, hindering residents' ability to track the restoration process. Power outage tracker maps provided by various outlets, including the Houston Chronicle, FOX 26 Houston, and USA TODAY, offer real-time updates on the affected areas. CenterPoint Energy has estimated that power restoration for most customers will take several days. Despite efforts to restore power, CenterPoint Energy has warned customers to be prepared for extended outages. Residents are encouraged to report outages and stay informed through the company's website and social media channels.

name: Longlegs
summary: Several reviews have been released for the new horror film "Longlegs," offering a range of opinions. "Awards Radar" and "Variety" highly praise the film as a "serial killer horror masterpiece" and a "dread-filled" thriller that "worms his way into your nightmares." Other reviews are more mixed, with "The Film Stage" criticizing its "too clean" execution and "Evening Standard" finding it "disappointing." However, many reviewers acknowledge the strong performances of Nicolas Cage and Maika Monroe, with "Hollywood Reporter" describing their performances as "a mesmerizing serial killer chiller that burns with Satanic power." Despite its flaws, "Longlegs" seems to have made a mark with its creepy and disturbing atmosphere, leaving a lasting impact on those who have seen it.

name: Novak Djokovic
summary: Novak Djokovic's Wimbledon campaign continues with a knee issue that hasn't fully resolved but a successful victory over Holger Rune. Despite his mobility concerns, Djokovic has praised Rune's "spectacular" performance. However, Djokovic has expressed dissatisfaction with the Wimbledon crowd, accusing them of "disrespect" during his match against Rune. Djokovic claimed the crowd's booing was disrespectful, but some have defended the fans, suggesting their reaction may have been due to Djokovic's past vaccination stance. Despite the crowd controversy, Djokovic remains focused on his goal of breaking records, as expressed by Roger Federer.

name: Jay Johnston
summary: Jay Johnston, an actor known for his roles in "Anchorman" and "Bob's Burgers," has pleaded guilty to a felony charge related to his involvement in the January 6, 2021 attack on the U.S. Capitol. Johnston admitted to interfering with police officers during the riot, charges that stem from his participation in the mob that forcefully entered the Capitol building in an attempt to overturn the results of the 2020 presidential election. This plea represents a significant development in the ongoing investigations and legal proceedings surrounding the Capitol attack.

name: Agatha All Along
summary: The long-awaited trailer for "Agatha All Along," the highly anticipated Marvel spinoff series, has finally arrived. Kathryn Hahn reprises her role as the fan-favorite witch Agatha Harkness, who was first introduced in "WandaVision." The trailer promises a thrilling and intriguing story, with Agatha investigating the mysterious death of Wanda and teaming up with a new character played by Aubrey Plaza. The trailer also features plenty of Easter eggs and references to the Marvel Cinematic Universe, making it a must-watch for fans. "Agatha All Along" is set to premiere on Disney+ in early 2024.
